  "prompt": "What is the best iOS calendar app that allows you to cross off EVENTS as you go through the day?",
  "response": "There are several great iOS calendar apps that allow you to manage your events effectively, and some of them even let you cross off events as you complete them. Here are a few popular options that you might consider:\n\n1. **Todoist**: While primarily a task management app, Todoist integrates with calendars and lets you check off tasks/events as you complete them. You can create scheduled tasks to function similarly to calendar events.\n\n2. **Google Calendar**: Although it doesn't have a built-in feature to cross off events directly, you could create events as tasks and then mark them complete. Integrating it with other apps like Todoist can enhance the functionality.\n\n3. **Things 3**: This is a highly-rated task management app that allows you to create events for your day and check them off as you complete them. It has a great interface and is very user-friendly.\n\n4. **Fantastical**: This app combines calendars and tasks in one place, allowing you to manage your events and tasks easily. You can mark tasks as completed, which is useful for tracking what you've done throughout the day.\n\n5. **Microsoft To Do**: This app integrates with Outlook Calendar and allows you to manage tasks and events. You can easily check off completed items.\n\n6. **Apple Reminders with Calendar integration**: You can create reminders for events and check them off as you go, using the built-in Apple ecosystem to sync with your calendars.\n\nEach of these apps has its unique features, so it may be worth trying a couple to see which one best fits your workflow.",
